k to the documentation of grpc-java. There are also ambiguities about public vs. internal classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test coverage**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether to add a test for `InternalCheckGcpEnvironment.isOnGcp()`. It returns a boolean but it's tricky to assert the environment. I could check if it's stable between calls, as it reads a sys file under native conditions. Also, I might want to test `AltsChannelBuilder.forTarget` since existing tests only use `forAddress`. But does that make it too similar to what’s already covered? I need to be mindful not to duplicate tests, yet adding missing factory variants could be justified.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating service registration tests**\\n\\nI'm realizing that the existing tests for `AltsServerBuilder` cover forwarding options but not service registration or interceptors. Since the method is public, I could build and start a server to assert that `server.getServices()` includes the correct service after it starts. I don't need a client for this. However, I’m concerned about whether this test would duplicate the checks already in place, especially since it will inherently involve starting the server again. It might be a slight overlap.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8jwx2IVseg1rEISXDJr7lm1p|fc_062a81f5b6aa58660169fd0ab666f08197ad2d8ae28cbd88b0", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/io.grpc/grpc-api/1.71.0/*/grpc-api-1.71.0.jar -public io.grpc.Server | sed -n '1,120p'"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 849, "output": 1207, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31240, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778191007887, "responseId": "resp_062a81f5b6aa58660169fd0aa142a08197b2d0fabe73d67271"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_8jwx2IVseg1rEISXDJr7lm1p|fc_062a81f5b6aa58660169fd0ab666f08197ad2d8ae28cbd88b0", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compiled from \"Server.java\"\npublic abstract class io.grpc.Server {\n  public io.grpc.Server();\n  public abstract io.grpc.Server start() throws java.io.IOException;\n  public int getPort();\n  public java.util.List<? extends java.net.SocketAddress> getListenSockets();\n  public java.util.List<io.grpc.ServerServiceDefinition> getServices();\n  public java.util.List<io.grpc.ServerServiceDefinition> getImmutableServices();\n  public java.util.List<io.grpc.ServerServiceDefinition> getMutableServices();\n  public abstract io.grpc.Server shutdown();\n  public abstract io.grpc.Server shutdownNow();\n  public abstract boolean isShutdown();\n  public abstract boolean isTerminated();\n  public abstract boolean awaitTermination(long, java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit) throws java.lang.InterruptedException;\n  public abstract void awaitTermination() throws java.lang.InterruptedException;\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778191031764}]}
